I very much appreciate the switch from italics to straight letters, above. To extract a bit more of the HTML, <span class="comment">(<a href="#FOO">â†’</a>â€Ž<span dir="auto"><span class="autocomment">BAR: </span> FOOBAR</span>)</span>. I think there probably is a way for CSS to take care of this, since FOOBAR is outside the span for italics. #comment should inherit rather than italicize, while #autocomment should italicize. @Edokter: Do you think that would work re specificity (I suppose that's a case of checking the core css?). --Izno (talk) 12:43, 29 January 2016 (UTC)

